00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.360
[Basics of Cloud Computing - Module 2: Cloud Service Models] Unlock the power of the cloud with its service models!

00:00:03.760 --> 00:00:37.310
[Cloud Service Models Overview] In today's lesson, we will explore the three main cloud service models: IaaS, PaaS, and SaaS. Each model offers unique benefits and capabilities that cater to different needs and scenarios. Have you ever wondered how businesses deploy applications without managing their own infrastructure? That’s where these models come into play. By understanding each service model, you can better determine which one suits your project requirements. Let's dive in and demystify cloud computing together!

00:00:37.710 --> 00:01:11.310
[What is IaaS?] Let's start with IaaS, Infrastructure as a Service. IaaS lets you rent IT infrastructure—like servers and storage—over the internet. For example, Amazon Web Services (AWS) offers EC2 instances that allow businesses to run their applications without investing heavily in physical servers. This model is highly scalable: you can adjust your resources based on demand. Think of it as renting a workshop; you pay only for the space you use. Does it sound beneficial for a startup needing flexibility? Absolutely!

00:01:11.710 --> 00:01:46.220
[What is PaaS?] Next up is PaaS, or Platform as a Service. This model provides a platform allowing developers to build, run, and manage applications without the complexity of building and maintaining the infrastructure. Google App Engine is a prime example, enabling developers to focus on code instead of worrying about servers. So, why choose PaaS? Because it significantly speeds up the development process, allowing teams to deploy applications faster. Does your project require quick iteration and deployment? PaaS might just be what you need!

00:01:46.620 --> 00:02:20.440
[What is SaaS?] Finally, we have SaaS, Software as a Service. This model delivers software over the internet on a subscription basis. Think of tools like Microsoft 365 or Salesforce; you access them online without worrying about installation or maintenance. SaaS is all about convenience and lowers the barrier to entry for software access. This makes it perfect for users who want to utilize software without the headache of updates. Are you ready to leverage SaaS for your projects? Embrace the ease of use it brings!

00:02:20.840 --> 00:02:24.150
[Next Steps] Explore which cloud service model fits your needs best!
